message: Welcome! Here's what I learned: Always use the 'growth serum' exactly once on each individual animal. Large animals (like lion, giraffe, whale, panda) give 15 value, medium (octopus, kangaroo, monkey) give 10, and small (bee, butterfly, trout, bird, lizard, pufferfish) give 5. This is your safest positive gain. The 'mutation catalyst' is very bad, avoid it entirely. Combining two individual 'grown' animals can yield high positive values, especially combinations like (large land + medium water/land) or (large land + large land) which consistently gave 30 points (e.g., grown whale + grown monkey, grown lion + grown giraffe). However, combining two items that are *already combined* results in a massive negative value, so NEVER do that. Do not apply growth serum more than once to any single item. Submit when you have your highest value item from the safe strategies, before risking combining complex items or using the catalyst.

message: The previous player's advice about the mutation catalyst and multiple growth serums was accurate; avoid the catalyst entirely, and only use growth serum once per initial ingredient. The most reliable strategy is to use the growth serum once on *each individual ingredient* first. Larger animals (elephant, giraffe, panda, whale, shark) generally yield 15 points with growth, medium (monkey, squid, snake, crab) yield 10, and small (bee, butterfly, bird) yield 5. After all ingredients are grown, combine two *grown* items. The highest values come from combining grown items that live in *different environments*, especially land animals with water animals (e.g., grown elephant + grown shark = 35). Combining items from the same environment (e.g., grown monkey + grown zebra = 20) or items from the air (grown bee + grown butterfly = 10) yields lower but still positive values. Crucially, *do not combine items that are already combined* (e.g., a grown monkey-zebra hybrid with a grown flying squidbee); this resulted in a severely negative value in my playthrough.
